label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific tumor necrosis factor (ligand) superfamily member 11 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific tumor necrosis factor (ligand) superfamily member 11 production by T cells that detects tumor necrosis factor production.

label.value: purified MHC direct binding assay of a MHC:ligand complex using radioactivity detection

definition.value: A purified MHC binding assay that uses radioactivity detection to measure direct ligand binding.

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-8 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-8 production by T cells that uses an intracellular cytokine staining assay.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific intracellular cytokine staining (ICS) IL-223 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-23 production by T cells that uses a cytometric bead array assay.

label.value: obsolete purified MHC direct binding assay

definition.value: direct binding assay measuring MHC ligand binding using MHC derived from a purified MHC molecule preparation

label.value: epitope specific vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells

definition.value: A process of vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: purified MHC competitive binding assay measuring half maximal inhibitory concentration [IC50] of a MHC:ligand complex using fluorescence detection

definition.value: A purified MHC ligand binding half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50) determination assay that uses fluorescence detection to detect loss of binding of a known reference ligand due to competition by the ligand under investigation.

label.value: GenBank ID

definition.value: A CRID symbol uniquely indentifies the submitted GeneBank sequence record.

label.value: investigation description

definition.value: A textual entity that describes an investigation.

label.value: specimen identifier

definition.value: A CRID symbol denotes a specimen and used to distinguish one specimen from another in an investigation.

label.value: PubMed ID

definition.value: A CRID symbol that is sufficient to look up a citation from the PubMed, a literature database of life sciences and biomedical information.

label.value: average depth of sequence coverage

definition.value: An average value of the depth of sequence coverage based both on external (e.g. Cot-based size estimates) and internal (average coverage in the assembly) measures of genome size.

label.value: specimen collection time measurement datum

definition.value: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the time when the specimens are collected.

label.value: latitude coordinate measurement datum

definition.value: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

label.value: longitude coordinate measurement datum

definition.value: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

label.value: investigation title

definition.value: A textual entity that denotes an investigation.

label.value: organism identification objective

definition.value: A biological feature identification objective to identify the organism species in a specimen.

label.value: organism identification assay

definition.value: An assay that identifies the organism species in a specimen.

label.value: sequence annotation algorithm

definition.value: An algorithm used to identify sequence features (e.g. protein coding regions) in the assembled contig sequence.  This may also include a description of any manual curation that may have generated or validated the annotation.

label.value: Bioinformatics Resource Center

definition.value: An organization that  is one of the Internet-based research centers established and funded by NIAID (the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases). The Bioinformatics Resource Centers (BRCs) were formed in response to the threats posed by emerging and re-emerging pathogens, particularly CDC Category A, B, and C pathogens, and their potential use in bioterrorism. The intention of NIAID in funding these bioinformatics centers is to assist researchers involved in the experimental characterization of such pathogens and the formation of drugs, vaccines, or diagnostic tools to combat them.

label.value: country name

definition.value: A textual entity that denotes a geographic location that is a site or part of a site that is identified as a country in the political geography.

label.value: investigation identifier

definition.value: A CRID symbol used to identify an investigation.

label.value: grant identifier

definition.value: A CRID symbol used to identify a grant.

label.value: analytical chromatography

definition.value: An analyte assay that uses a biomaterial's preferential affinity for either the mobile phase or the stationary phase to separate it from other materials and thereby detect its presence in an input material.

label.value: electron microscopy imaging assay

definition.value: An imaging assay in which an electrons are used to probe the density, shape and composition of an input material which are detected in an electron microscope and utilized to produce an image of the material.

label.value: immuno staining assay

definition.value: A assay detecting a molecular label assay in which the label is attached to an antibody so that substances are marked based on the antibody's binding specificity.

label.value: purified material

definition.value: A material entity that is generated by a purification process in which an input material is separated to obtain a fraction with a higher concentration of a desired component

label.value: calorimetric binding assay

definition.value: A binding assay in which the heat generated or absorbed during a binding event is measured, which allows determination of binding constants, reaction stoichiometry, enthalpy and entropy.

label.value: antibody binding detection by fluorescence quenching

definition.value: A binding assay in which affinity is measured by detecting a change in fluorescence (usually quenching) that occurs upon binding of the antibody to the ligand. The fluorescent signal that is affected by binding is either from an exogenous fluorophore attached to the ligand, or is the intrisic fluorescence of aromatic (tryptophan) residues on the binding site of the antibody (no conjugated fluorophore necessary) or, less commonly, on the ligand binding region (epitope).

label.value: grant

definition.value: A plan specification of organization A to give money to organization B so that B conducts investigations. Organization A has funder role and Organization B has research organization role.

label.value: antigen inhibition assay measuring the dissociation constant [KD] of a B cell epitope:antibody complex approximated by IC50

definition.value: A B cell epitope equilibrium dissociation constant (KD) assay that provides IC50 values determined under assay conditions where the IC50 approximates a KD value using a B cell epitope antigen inhibition of binding assay.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific Ig-mediated histamine release

definition.value: A B cell epitope specific activation of additional immune response in vitro assay that detects histamine release.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific immunoglobulin-mediated antigen activation

definition.value: A B cell epitope dependent biological activity determination assay that detects antigen activation.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific complement-dependent cytotoxicity

definition.value: A B cell epitope specific activation of additional immune response in vitro assay that detects complement-dependent cytotoxicity.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity

definition.value: A B cell epitope specific activation of additional immune response in vitro assay that detects antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific immunoglobulin-mediated neutralization

definition.value: A B cell epitope dependent biological activity determination assay that detects neutralization of the antigen.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific opsonization

definition.value: A B cell epitope specific activation of additional immune response in vitro assay that detects opsonization.

label.value: calorimetry assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses a calorimetric binding assay.

label.value: electron microscopy assay determining the 3D structure of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope 3D structure determination assay that uses an electron microscopy imaging assay.

label.value: NMR assay determining the 3D structure of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope 3D structure determination assay that uses a nuclear magnetic resonance assay.

label.value: cross blocking assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses an antibody cross-blocking assay.

label.value: RIA measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses a radio immuno assay.

label.value: immunoblot assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses an immunoblot assay.

label.value: plasmon resonance assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses a surface plasmon resonance assay.

label.value: immuno staining assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses an immuno staining assay.

label.value: immunoprecipitation assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses an immunoprecipitation assay.

label.value: mass spectrometry assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses a mass spectrometry assay.

label.value: phage display assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses a phage display binding assay.

label.value: electron microscopy assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses an electron microscopy imaging assay.

label.value: ELISA measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope qualitative binding to antibody assay that uses an enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay.
